From 7eebe334d127f4f34e3e179f6905a4618d50c1dd Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jake Teton-Landis <just.1.jake@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 8 Jul 2026 14:27:50 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] External-signals seam: render identity for external
 stores

One injectable runtime (pass started/discarded, commit phases bracketing
the DOM mutation window exactly, per-root committed lanes) plus three
inbound helpers: a forced update lane so corrective re-renders join a live
batch's own commit, the current transition scope's lane for batch keying,
and a root-lane kick that guarantees every batch a close edge. Existence
of the react-dom 'unstable_externalSignals' export is the handshake.
